./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:8439:The runner unit is intended to be long-lived. It uses `Restart=always` so a clean `sdp-cli run` exit immediately re-enters the queue loop, while maintenance-gated launcher exits use code `75` and are treated as successful non-restarting stops.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:8448:This probe is platform-aware: it checks `launchctl` on macOS homes and `systemctl` on Linux homes so status checks do not crash when the local service manager is absent.
